Pope Francis has said climate change is a challenge of "epochal proportions" and that the world must convert to clean fuel. "Civilisation requires energy, but energy use must not destroy civilisation," he said, speaking to a group of oil company executives at the end of a two-day conference in the Vatican. ALSO READ:

